<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='368000' id='t-368000'>into an electrical signal.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='370000' id='t-370000'>And that signal is then converted back</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='372000' id='t-372000'>to a high-speed data stream.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='374000' id='t-374000'>In the future we hope</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='376000' id='t-376000'>that we can integrate this little hole</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='378000' id='t-378000'>into these smart phones.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='381000' id='t-381000'>And not only integrate a photo detector here,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='384000' id='t-384000'>but maybe use the camera inside.</span>
</span>
</p>
<p class='talk-transcript__para'>
<data class='talk-transcript__para__time'>
 6:39
</data>
<span class='talk-transcript__para__text'>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='388000' id='t-388000'>So what happens</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='390000' id='t-390000'>when I switch on that light?</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='395000' id='t-395000'>As you would expect,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='397000' id='t-397000'>it's a light, a desk lamp.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='399000' id='t-399000'>Put your book beneath it and you can read.</span>
